The paper discusses the relationship between dependency distance and parsing, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of natural language processing in informing research on dependency distance, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper touches on the evolution of human languages, which could fall under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SD).
